The paper deals with facial expression recognition using convolutional neural networks and bag-of-visual-words model, which are both computer vision techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as k-nearest neighbors and Support Vector Machines, which fall under the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of deep learning models such as convolutional neural networks also suggests the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves the fusion of handcrafted and deep features, which could fall under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
